== 游戏玩法 ==
[[File:Final_Fantasy_Dimensions_Battle.jpg|thumb]]
《最终幻想传奇：光与暗的战士》是一款在以往16位[[最终幻想系列|最终幻想系列]]游戏基础上开发的[[電子角色扮演遊戲|角色扮演游戏]]。游戏采用{{tsl|en|Active Time Battle||回合战斗}}系统，在战斗过程中每一个角色的计时由一个随着时间的推移而不停充满的量表负责。一旦某个角色的量表充满，玩家就可以在这个特定的角色身上选择一个指令。在选择指令过后，角色的量表会再次开始填充以执行该指令。一旦量表再次填满并执行完指令后，量表将会清空并再次重复执行之前的一系列动作<!--''Final Fantasy Dimensions'' is a [[role-playing_video_game|role-playing video game]], developed in the style of previous 16-bit ''[[Final_Fantasy|Final Fantasy]]'' games. The game uses the {{tsl|en|Active Time Battle}} system in which a character's turn are determined by a gauge that fills over time during battle. Once the gauge fills completely from one character, players can choose a command from that specific character. After choosing a command, the gauge fills over again to execute the command. Once the gauge fills again and the command is executed, the gauge empties and repeats the cycle.--><ref name="1UPpreview">{{cite web |last=Parish |first=Jeremy |title=FF Legends: Hands-on with the Latest "Classic" Final Fantasy |url=http://www.1up.com/previews/legends-hands-on-latest-classic-final |language=en |publisher=[[1UP.com|1UP.com]] |accessdate=2013-10-31 |date=2010-09-24 |archive-date=2012-07-27 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/69ShdXFR5?url=http://www.1up.com/previews/legends-hands-on-latest-classic-final |dead-url=no }}</ref>。与《[[最终幻想IV_The_After_-月之归还-|最终幻想IV The After -月之归还-]]》相似，本作采用分章节发布，但是玩家必须按照顺序来游玩每一个游戏章节<!-- Similar to ''[[Final_Fantasy_IV:_The_After_Years|Final Fantasy IV: The After Years]]'', the game was released in an episodic format, but players must play through each episode in sequence.--><ref name="Siliconera-details">{{cite web |author=Spencer |title=These Are The Heroes Of Final Fantasy Legends: Warriors Of Light And Darkness |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2010/08/20/these-are-the-heroes-of-final-fantasy-legends-warriors-of-light-and-darkness/ |language=en |publisher=Siliconera |accessdate=2013-10-30 |date=2010-08-20 |archive-date=2013-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131116073250/http://www.siliconera.com/2010/08/20/these-are-the-heroes-of-final-fantasy-legends-warriors-of-light-and-darkness/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。玩家可以组建一支五人队伍，在每一章节的开始时可以变更队伍的成员构成<!-- Players command a party of five with the party members changing in each episode.--><ref name="5-party">{{cite web |last=Sadewo |first=Bams |title=Square Enix to release Final Fantasy Dimensions in summer |url=http://www.androidauthority.com/square-enix-to-release-final-fantasy-dimensions-in-summer-104274/ |language=en |publisher=Android Authority |accessdate=2013-10-30 |date=2012-07-30 |archive-date=2013-02-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130215223209/http://www.androidauthority.com/square-enix-to-release-final-fantasy-dimensions-in-summer-104274/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

游戏采用一种与《[[最终幻想V|最终幻想V]]》中相类似的[[Job_System|职业系统]]作为战斗的基础。游戏允许玩家改变职业，并同时保留之前已获得的技能。在达到一定数量的AP之后当前的职业可以获得特定的职业技能。这些习得的技能可以在玩家变换不同职业的时候被装备上。在特定的时间下，玩家能装备的技能数量是有限制的，这种限制随着玩家职业的升级而逐渐放宽。在游戏中，玩家也可以通过设置某些能力的组合形成“合成能力”。<!--The game uses a {{tsl|en|Job System}} similar to ''[[Final_Fantasy_V|Final Fantasy V]]'' as a base of its battles. The game allows players to change job while still retaining skills that have already been acquired. Job-specific abilities can be learned after crossing a certain amount of AP for the current job given. That learned ability can be set even if the player changes to a different job. Players are limited in how many abilities they can set at a given time. This limit rises as the job's level rises. The game also has "Fusion Abilities" which players can form by setting combinations of certain abilities.--><ref name="Job-system">{{cite web|title=Final Fantasy Legends Job System Detailed |url=http://andriasang.com/comoyf/ff_legends_job_system/ |publisher=Andrasang |accessdate=2013-10-31 |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121225024938/http://andriasang.com/comoyf/ff_legends_job_system/ |archivedate=2012-12-25 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>

从游戏的一开始就提供有全部的八种主要职业：[[自由人|自由人]]、[[战士|战士]]、[[Final_Fantasy_character_classes#Monk|武僧]]、[[盗贼|盗贼]]、[[赤魔法師|赤魔法師]]、[[白魔法師|白魔法師]]、[[黑魔法師|黑魔法師]]以及[[召唤士|召唤士]]。在完成每一章节的关卡后都会解锁一种新的职业。光之战士的未解锁职业有（依照章節按照順序排列）：[[龙骑士|龙骑士]]、[[吟游诗人|吟游诗人]]、[[記憶士|記憶士]]、[[騎士|騎士]]以及[[導師|導師]]，而暗之战士的未解锁职业有（依照章節按照順序排列）：[[獵人|獵人]]、[[暗黑騎士|暗黑騎士]]、[[舞者|舞者]]、[[忍者|忍者]]以及[[巫師|巫師]]。<!--
The Jobs available from the beginning for all the eight main characters are {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Freelancer|Freelancer}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Warrior|Warrior}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Monk|Monk}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Thief|Thief}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Red Mage|Red Mage}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#White Mage|White Mage}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Black Mage|Black Mage}}, and {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Summoner|Summoner}}. Each episode introduces a new Job, which is unlocked after completing the episode. The unlockable jobs for the Warriors of Light are {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Dragoon|Dragoon}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Bard|Bard}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Memorist|Memorist}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Paladin|Paladin}}, and {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Devout|Seer}}, while the jobs unlocked for the Warriors of Darkness are {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Hunter|Ranger}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Dark Knight|Dark Knight}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Dancer|Dancer}}, {{tsl|en|Final Fantasy character classes#Ninja|Ninja}}, and Magus.--><ref name="Job-system" />

== 开发 ==
本作由曾负责史克威尔艾尼克斯公司旗下首款[[手机游戏|手机游戏]]《[[最终幻想IV_The_After_-月之归还-|最终幻想IV The After -月之归还-]]》的原班制作团队操刀。<!--The game was developed by the same internal Square Enix team that made [[Final_Fantasy_IV:_The_After_Years|Final Fantasy IV: The After Years]], which was also initially a game for Japanese cell phones. -->由秋山纪夫负责监制、时田贵司担纲制作人。<!--The game was directed by Toshio Akiyama and produced by Takashi Tokita. -->角色设定由Akira Oguro负责，而角色的2D[[点阵|点阵]]版本则由{{tsl|en|Kazuko Shibuya||涉谷员子}}负责创建。时田贵司解释说，本作是为了超越人们对手机平台[[电子角色扮演游戏|角色扮演游戏]]的期望而生<!--Character designs were provided by Akira Oguro while the in-game 2D dot versions were created by Kazuko Shibuya. Takashi Tokita explained the game was meant to transcend the expectations of RPGs in cellphones.--><ref>{{cite web|last=Gantayat |first=Anoop |title=Final Fantasy Legends Detailed |url=http://andriasang.com/comn77/ff_legends_detailed/ |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130410125132/http://andriasang.com/comn77/ff_legends_detailed/ |archivedate=2013-04-10 |publisher=Andriasang |accessdate=2013-03-14 |date=2010-07-26 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。制作团队以另一款[[SNES|SNES]]平台游戏的场景为制作主题。<!-- The team set the theme of a scenario of creating another game for the [[SNES|SNES]]. -->开发团队也在游戏中插入以往游戏的一些引用或者引申形象，例如参考自原版《[[最终幻想_(游戏)|最终幻想]]》游戏的Sarah和Matoya以及能让人联想起《[[最终幻想IV|最终幻想IV]]》中Palom和Porom的Dusk和Alba。<!--The team also added several references to previous games such as Sarah and Matoya being references to the original [[Final_Fantasy|Final Fantasy]] game and Dusk and Alba being reminiscent of Palom and Porom from [[Final_Fantasy_IV|Final Fantasy IV]]. When asked about the high pricing for the game, the team explained their reasons stating,-->当被问及游戏的高售价时，游戏的制作团队解释说“本作提供了约50小时的游戏时长，我们觉得我们的玩家社群将可以在本作中获得如在主机平台上一样丰富的游戏体验。此外，目前之所以定制这样的价格，是因为本作是专门为移动平台而开发的游戏，并非以往作品仅仅是旧主机平台或掌机平台版本的移植游戏。”<!-- "This title offers about 50 hours of gameplay, and we feel that our community can enjoy the contents of this game as much as they would a console title. Also, we have set the price where it is because this title was developed specifically for the mobile platform, as opposed to just being a port of an older console or handheld game."--><ref>{{cite web |author=By Spencer |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2013/01/17/final-fantasy-dimensions-was-square-enixs-take-on-a-new-snes-ff-game/ |title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Was Square Enix's Take On A New SNES FF Game |publisher=Siliconera |date=2013-01-17 |accessdate=2013-02-19 |archive-date=2013-02-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130222075522/http://www.siliconera.com/2013/01/17/final-fantasy-dimensions-was-square-enixs-take-on-a-new-snes-ff-game/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>在开发智能手机版本时，监制时田贵司改变了销售方式，以一组章节打包发售，而不是分开单独发售<!--一改单独分章发售的销售模式，采用打包When developing the smartphone version, Takashi Tokita changed the structure of selling a group of episodes rather than individually.--><ref name="DimensionsDetails">{{cite web|title=SQEXスマホ用新作『FF ディメンションズ』、『DEMONS’ SCORE』の 詳細に迫る！ 時田貴司氏インタビュー【E3 2012】|url=http://www.famitsu.com/news/201206/08015998.html|language=ja|publisher=Famitsu|accessdate=2013-03-11|date=2012-06-08|archive-date=2013-01-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130129104431/http://www.famitsu.com/news/201206/08015998.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 音乐 ==
除去部分先前由[[植松伸夫|植松伸夫]]创作的歌曲，大部分的游戏音乐由[[水田直志|水田直志]]完成。水田旨在将音乐创作的更接近先前的最终幻想游戏中那种类似可以被哼唱的一段固定旋律的风格。为了使游戏中每一章节的音乐有所变化，他也尝试使游戏部分背景轻送愉快的《光之章》中的音乐与背景沉重黑暗的《暗之章》中的音乐有所区别<!--Naoshi Mizuta composed the music of Final Fantasy Dimensions with the exception of a number of songs previously composed by Nobuo Uematsu. Naoshi intended to compose the music closer to previous Final Fantasy games such as a solid melody that can be hummed or whistled. Naoshi also made it so that the Light chapters would have different music from the Dark chapters in order to have variation of music between chapters.--><ref name= "famitsu-interview">{{cite web |url= http://www.famitsu.com/news/201108/18048249.html |title= 『ファイナルファンタジー レジェンズ 光と闇の戦士』完結記念！ 時田プロデューサーら5名にミニインタビュー！ |publisher= Famitsu |language= ja |accessdate= 2013-03-05 |archive-date= 2014-03-22 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20140322164449/http://www.famitsu.com/news/201108/18048249.html |dead-url= no }}</ref>。为庆祝游戏制作的完成，2011年8月8日在日本地区以数字下载的形式发布了名为《{{nihongo|最终幻想传奇：光与暗的战士原声大碟|ファイナルファンタジー レジェンズ 光と闇の戦士 オリジナル・サウンドトラック}}》的游戏原声大碟<!--
A soundtrack for the game titled {{nihongo|Final Fantasy Legends: Hikari to Yami no Senshi Original Soundtrack|ファイナルファンタジー レジェンズ 光と闇の戦士 オリジナル・サウンドトラック}} was released digitally in Japan on August 8, 2011 to celebrate the completion of the game.--><ref name="Finale2+OST">{{cite web |url=http://www.famitsu.com/news/201108/08048167.html |title=『ファイナルファンタジー レジェンズ 光と闇の戦士』最後の追加シ ナリオ配信開始、サントラも配信へ |publisher=Famitsu |language=ja |accessdate=2013-03-05 |archive-date=2013-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203001140/http://www.famitsu.com/news/201108/08048167.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。而名为《{{nihongo|世界的去向 from Final Fantasy Legends|セカイノユクエ from FINAL FANTASY LEGENDS}}》的[[EP|EP]]则于2012年8月31日在日本的[[iTunes|iTunes]]以及[[mora|mora]]音乐商店以数字版发售<!-- An [[EP|EP]] soundtrack titled {{nihongo|Sekainoyukue from Final Fantasy Legends|セカイノユクエ from FINAL FANTASY LEGENDS}} was also released digitally in Japan on [[iTunes|iTunes]] and {{tsl|en|Mora (music store)|mora}} music store on August 31, 2012.--><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/jp/album/sekainoyukue-from-final-fantasy/id553777482|title=セカイノユクエ from FINAL FANTASY LEGENDS - EP|publisher=Square Enix|language=ja|accessdate=2013-03-14|archive-date=2014-02-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227113355/https://itunes.apple.com/jp/album/sekainoyukue-from-final-fantasy/id553777482|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 发行历史 ==
本作最早开端于史克威尔艾尼克斯注册了商标“Final Fantasy Legends: Hikari to Yami no Senshi”，这个商标最早被认为是《{{tsl|en|Tactics Ogre: Let Us Cling Together||皇家骑士团}}》相关的作品<!--The game was initially hinted when Square Enix trademarked Hikari to Yami no Senshi which was initially believed to be related to {{tsl|en|Tactics Ogre: Let Us Cling Together}}.--><ref name="Trademark">{{cite web|author=Spencer |title=The Latest Square Enix Trademark Is Warrior Of Light And Darkness |url=http://andriasang.com/commzs/ff_legends_announced/ |publisher=Siliconera |accessdate=2013-04-09 |date=2010-05-17 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121225021341/http://andriasang.com/commzs/ff_legends_announced/ |archivedate=2012-12-25 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。2010年7月21日在日本以《最终幻想传奇：光与暗的战士》之名公布<!--It was announced in Japan as Final Fantasy Legends: Hikari to Yami no Senshi on July 21, 2010.--><ref name="ASannounce">{{cite web|last=Gantayat |first=Anoop |title=Final Fantasy Legends Formally Announced |url=http://andriasang.com/commzs/ff_legends_announced/ |publisher=Andriasang |accessdate=2011-03-08 |date=2010-07-21 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121225021341/http://andriasang.com/commzs/ff_legends_announced/ |archivedate=2012-12-25 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。游戏的第一章节最先在2010年9月6日发布于iMode手机平台，之后在2010年12月9日发布于EZweb手机平台<!-- The first chapters of the game were first released for iMode phones on September 6, 2010, and for EZweb phones on December 9, 2010.--><ref name="QJ">{{cite web|title=Final Fantasy Legends: Warriors of Light and Darkness detailed|url=http://www.finalfantasyunion.com/news/final-fantasy-legend-warrior-of-light-and-darkness-detailed--1038.html|author=Colin|publisher=Final Fantasy Union|date=Jul 21, 2010|accessdate=2013-10-30|language=en|archive-date=2015-09-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924012949/http://www.finalfantasyunion.com/news/final-fantasy-legend-warrior-of-light-and-darkness-detailed--1038.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在此之后，iMode平台自2011年8月8日起、EZweb平台自2011年11月10日起，以每月一章的速度发布余下的章节。2011年东京游戏展上，本作公布将在提升画面和音质之后再iOS和Android平台上发售，同时也支持[[功能手机|功能手机]]上使用模拟摇杆外设<!-- The rest of the chapters were released approximately once a month since then till August 8, 2011 for iMode and November 10, 2011 for EZweb. On Tokyo Game Show of 2011, the game was announced to be released on iOS and Android with improved graphics and sound, and support for slide-pad controls over the 功能手机 version.--><ref>{{cite web|title=Final Fantasy Legends Hits iOS and Android This Summer |url=http://andriasang.com/con1kv/ff_legends_smartphone/ |publisher=Andriasang |accessdate=2012-06-22 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121225082320/http://andriasang.com/con1kv/ff_legends_smartphone/ |archivedate=2012-12-25 |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。在2012年E3展会上，本作以《Final Fantasy Dimensions》之名发布iOS、Android平台国际版，包含[[简体中文|简体中文]]与[[繁体中文|繁体中文]]语言，并在2012年8月31日发售<!-- On E3 2012, the iOS/Android version was announced internationally as Final Fantasy Dimensions also to be released on August 31, 2012.--><ref name="DimensionsAnnounced">{{cite web |last=Schreier |first=Jason|title= Square Enix Is Releasing A Brand New, Original,Old-School Final Fantasy Game |url= http://kotaku.com/5916484/square-enix-is-releasing-a-brand-new-original-old%20school-final-fantasy-game |publisher=Kotaku |accessdate=2012-06-12 |date=2012-06-07|language=en}}</ref><ref name="DimensionsDate">{{cite web|last=Davis|first=Justin|title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Coming Later This Month|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/08/23/final-fantasy-dimensions-coming-later-this-month|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2013-11-08|language=en|date=August 23, 2012|archive-date=2012-08-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120825094831/http://www.ign.com/articles/2012/08/23/final-fantasy-dimensions-coming-later-this-month|dead-url=no}}</ref>。因技术故障，iOS版本首轮仅发布了《序章》。其他所有的章节在同一天稍后的时间在从1.0.0版本升级到1.0.1版本之后可以从应用商店购买下载<!--Due to technical difficulties, only "Prologue" was released first for the iOS version. All other chapters were purchasable at the in-app shop after upgrading from 1.0.0 to 1.0.1 which was available later in the same day.--><ref name="RPGFan1">{{cite web|title=Final Fantasy Dimensions now Available|url=http://www.rpgfan.com/news/2012/1856.html|publisher=RPGFan|accessdate=2013-11-08|date=08.31.12|language=en|archive-date=2012-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025092137/http://rpgfan.com/news/2012/1856.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。Android版本在2012年12月21日以完整版的形式发布<!--The Android version was released on December 21, 2012 in its complete form.--><ref>{{cite web|last=Patterson|first=Sean|title=Final Fantasy Dimensions Released for Android|date=December 21, 2012|url=http://www.webpronews.com/final-fantasy-dimensions-released-for-android-2012-12|publisher=Web Pro News|accessdate=2013-11-08|language=en|archive-date=2013-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130403231118/http://www.webpronews.com/final-fantasy-dimensions-released-for-android-2012-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

